    <summary>08/10/1993: A Chinese passenger onboard an Air China flight from Beijing threatened to pour acid over passengers unless the flight changed course to Taiwan. Air China Flight CA973 left Beijing at 09:51 (Beijing time) and was hijacked at 11:15 (Beijing time). At this time, the plane was diverted to Taiwan and landed at the Taipei international airport, where the lone hijacker exited. The crew with all its passengers (save for the hijacker) returned to Xiamen, China at 16:03 (Beijing time). No one was injured.</summary>
